+## WALLET-210 Staging Partner Pilot Dry Run
+
+Run this dry run before a 211 service partner pilot, after changing partner
+grant policy, after changing proof UI exposure, and after changing approved
+analytics templates used by the pilot. Use synthetic wallet data and a
+synthetic or approved staging service directory. Do not use real client records
+as readiness evidence.
+
+Required setup:
+
+- Target staging uses durable `WALLET_REPOSITORY_ROOT`, encrypted
+  `WALLET_STORAGE_CONFIG`, `WALLET_AUTO_LOAD_REPOSITORY=true`, and
+  `WALLET_AUTO_PERSIST=true`.
+- `WALLET_SERVICES_JSONL` points to the service directory used by the partner
+  pilot.
+- WALLET-170, WALLET-180, WALLET-190, and WALLET-200 evidence is archived or
+  explicitly tracked as a launch blocker.
+- The approved analytics template has consent copy, allowed derived fields,
+  k-threshold, privacy budget, retention mapping, reviewer roles, nullifier
+  policy, and withdrawal handling in the target signoff packet.
+
+Dry-run sequence:
+
+1. Create or load the synthetic wallet and add one document plus one precise
+   location. Evidence may include wallet ID, record IDs, ciphertext hashes,
+   storage status, and audit event IDs only.
+2. Create a partner access request for the document with a named purpose such
+   as `211_partner_document_review`. Approve it from recipient-access and
+   confirm the grant receipt contains the requested resource, ability, purpose,
+   and active status.
+3. From the partner recipient-access view, create redacted analysis. Confirm the
+   output has derived categories or summaries only and contains no plaintext
+   document text, names, emails, phone numbers, SSNs, or exact locations.
+4. Issue a coarse-location grant and invocation for service matching, then call
+   `/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/services/match`. Confirm the response identifies
+   eligible services without returning the wallet latitude or longitude.
+5. Create a location-region proof from the Proof Center. Confirm the public
+   inputs contain the claim, region ID, and policy/verifier identifiers, and do
+   not contain `lat`, `lon`, `witness`, target coordinates, or precise-address
+   values.
+6. Submit consent and a contribution for the approved aggregate analytics
+   template. Confirm `/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/proofs` contains an
+   `analytics_contribution` proof and that aggregate release still obeys the
+   approved k-threshold and privacy-budget policy.
+7. Revoke the partner access request or grant. Re-run the partner analysis
+   request and confirm it fails. Confirm revoked receipts are visible to the
+   partner and that `/ops/health` does not report revocation propagation errors.
+8. Open the Audit UI and fetch `/wallets/${WALLET_ID}/audit`. The timeline must
+   include `record/add`, `access/request`, `access/approve`,
+   `record/analyze_redacted`, `location/read_coarse`, `proof/create`,
+   `analytics/consent_create`, `analytics/contribute`, `grant/revoke`, and
+   `access/revoke`.
+
+Local validation:
+
+```bash
+pytest tests/test_wallet_interface_api.py tests/test_wallet_third_party_blackbox.py -q
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui run build
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui test -- tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts
+```
+
+Pass criteria: the commands pass, the full-stack browser run exercises Uploads,
+recipient-access, Proof Center, Group facts, and Audit against a live API, and
+the archived dry-run evidence contains no plaintext documents, direct
+identifiers, precise coordinates, proof witnesses, key material, or credential
+values.
+
