+## 211 Service Partner Pilot Reference
+
+WALLET-210 pilot readiness uses the public 211-AI wallet API and browser UI
+against the same `ipfs_datasets_py.wallet` service state. A partner pilot is
+ready to stage only when the workflow can be replayed with synthetic user data
+and the resulting audit timeline contains every user, partner, proof,
+analytics, and revocation step.
+
+Pilot data path:
+
+1. Create or load the user wallet with `POST /wallets`.
+2. Add the user document from the Uploads UI or
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/documents/text`; add precise location through
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/locations`. Precise location is encrypted wallet
+   data and is not a service-directory filter payload.
+3. Let the partner request document analysis with
+   `POST /wallets/{wallet_id}/access-requests`, using a concrete purpose such
+   as `211_partner_document_review`.
+4. Approve the request from the recipient-access UI. The resulting grant must
+   carry the request purpose and only the requested record resources and
+   abilities.
+5. Let the partner use the recipient-access UI to create redacted derived
+   analysis. The partner-facing result must not include document text, person
+   names, emails, phone numbers, SSNs, precise coordinates, or other direct
+   identifiers.
+6. For service matching, issue a `location/read_coarse` grant and invocation,
+   then call `/wallets/{wallet_id}/services/match`. The response may include
+   service IDs, names, coarse city/region reasons, and need matches; it must not
+   include the wallet latitude or longitude.
+7. For eligibility, create a location-region proof from the Proof Center or
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/locations/{location_record_id}/region-proofs`. Public
+   inputs are limited to claim, region, and policy/verifier identifiers. The
+   visible Proof Center continues to hide `location_distance` until target
+   verifier evidence is approved.
+8. For aggregate analytics, register an approved template, collect wallet
+   consent from the Group facts UI or consent API, and submit only approved
+   derived fields such as county and need category through
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/analytics/contributions`.
+9. Revoke the partner request from recipient-access or revoke the grant through
+   `/wallets/{wallet_id}/grants/{grant_id}/revoke`. Re-run the partner analysis
+   call and confirm it fails.
+10. Review `/wallets/{wallet_id}/audit` and the Audit UI for `record/add`,
+    `access/request`, `access/approve`, `record/analyze_redacted`,
+    `location/read_coarse`, `proof/create`, `analytics/consent_create`,
+    `analytics/contribute`, `grant/revoke`, and `access/revoke`.
+
+Pilot validation:
+
+```bash
+pytest tests/test_wallet_interface_api.py tests/test_wallet_third_party_blackbox.py -q
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui run build
+npm --prefix wallet_interface/ui test -- tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts
+```
+
+`wallet_interface/ui/tests/fullstack-wallet.spec.ts` starts a live API with
+local durable repository and encrypted blob storage, seeds a synthetic 211
+service directory through `WALLET_SERVICES_JSONL`, drives the Uploads,
+recipient-access, Proof Center, Group facts, and Audit browser surfaces, and
+checks public API responses for coordinate, witness, and direct-identifier
+leaks. Passing local validation is launch-supporting evidence; a target staging
+pilot still needs the production-readiness, verifier-cutover, retention, and
+analytics-governance evidence described above.
+
